solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    long long maximumTripletValue(vector<int>& nums) {
        long long maxVal = 0;
        int n = nums.size();
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 2; ++i) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n - 1; ++j) {
                long long diff = nums[i] - nums[j];
                if (diff <= 0) continue;
                for (int k = j + 1; k < n; ++k) {
                    long long val = diff * nums[k];
                    if (val > maxVal) maxVal = val;
                }
            }
        }
        return maxVal;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^3)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterate all valid triplets (i,j,k) with i<j<k, compute (nums[i]-nums[j])*nums[k], keep the maximum non-negative result. Early skip when diff≤0. With n≤100, the 161700 worst-case iterations are trivial.

